<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1832,2019]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,269,1832,1858]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Male.</emphasis>
Body length, 9.0–10.0 mm. Wing length, 
<quantity box="[795,944,1833,1859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="5.8">5.8–6.2 mm</quantity>
. General color brownish gray. Eyes and ocelli brownish yellow, facets homogenous, ocellar tubercle gray. Gena gray, clypeus bare and brown. Antenna brownish yellow arista darker; scape bare, half the length of pedicel; pedicel approximately oval; first flagellomere oval, as long as pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[647,765,1953,1979]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 60" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1431,1455]" captionTargetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[133,1454,194,1407]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 60. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Figure 
<number box="[733,765,1953,1979]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
), with many golden setae. Maxillary palpus long, slender (
<figureCitation box="[159,277,1993,2019]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 60" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1431,1455]" captionTargetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[133,1454,194,1407]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 60. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Figure 
<number box="[244,277,1993,2019]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="59.0">59</number>
</figureCitation>
). Proboscis and labella brownish to yellow. Occiput gray, with dark setae.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" targetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1431,1489]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,351,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">FIGURES 57–60.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[359,598,1432,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camargoi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[359,598,1432,1455]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName box="[359,488,1432,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysopilus</taxonomicName>
camargoi
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[607,669,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[607,669,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1541,2019]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Thorax dark brown, scutellum lighter than scutum, with many golden setae. Halter bare, knob yellowish, stem darker. Coxae brownish gray, femora and tibiae yellowish. Wing hyaline with antero-distal brownish macula (
<figureCitation box="[251,370,1621,1647]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 60" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1431,1455]" captionTargetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[133,1454,194,1407]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 60. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figure 
<number box="[337,370,1621,1647]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
); pterostigma rounded, large; areas around crossveins m-m and r-m pigmented; R 
<number box="[1330,1338,1637,1651]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1348,1355,1637,1651]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching C far from R 
<number box="[354,362,1680,1694]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
, with wide distal concavity; R 
<number box="[730,738,1680,1694]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.0">4</number>
forking with almost right angle, without short appendage, with distal fold toward anterior margin; CuA 
<number box="[672,680,1723,1737]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number box="[757,765,1723,1737]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
fusing far from margin; crossvein m-m far from origin of M 
<number box="[177,185,1766,1780]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1541,2019]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Abdomen brownish gray, with golden setae on tergites. Gonocoxite and gonostylus brown; gonocoxite longer than wide; gonostylus long, slightly rounded distally, covered with long setae, a group of fine setae medially; aedeagus long; ejaculatory and gonocoxal apodemes relatively short, gonocoxal apodeme curved outwards; lateral ejaculatory process wide, curved inward (
<figureCitation box="[863,984,1913,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,474,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[181,1406,474,1880]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 61 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 62 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 63 — Terminalia, ventral view, 64 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 65 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177245/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figure 
<number box="[952,984,1913,1939]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
); meso-anterior incision of tergite IX short (
<figureCitation box="[224,343,1953,1979]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,474,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[181,1406,474,1880]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 61 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 62 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 63 — Terminalia, ventral view, 64 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 65 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177245/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figure 
<number box="[310,343,1953,1979]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="62.0">62</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1541,2019]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1437,152,418]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,288,1992,2018]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Female</emphasis>
. Body length, 10.0 mm. Wing length, 7.0 mm. Gena yellowish gray. Thorax and abdomen similar to male. Anterior margin of sternite VIII rounded, hypogynial valves with 
<number box="[1032,1071,152,178]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7-8</number>
long setae (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1334,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,474,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[181,1406,474,1880]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 61 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 62 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 63 — Terminalia, ventral view, 64 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 65 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177245/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figure 
<number box="[1301,1334,152,178]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="64.0">64</number>
</figureCitation>
); genital fork with anterior portion acuminate, distal apodeme short and curved (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1140,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,474,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[181,1406,474,1880]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 61 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 62 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 63 — Terminalia, ventral view, 64 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 65 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177245/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figure 
<number box="[1107,1140,192,218]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="65.0">65</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus two-segmented, distal segment suboval (
<figureCitation box="[434,553,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,474,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[181,1406,474,1880]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 61 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 62 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 63 — Terminalia, ventral view, 64 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 65 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177245/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figure 
<number box="[520,553,232,258]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="63.0">63</number>
</figureCitation>
); long common spermathecal and spermathecal ducts; spermathecae spherical (
<figureCitation box="[208,327,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 60" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1431,1455]" captionTargetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[133,1454,194,1407]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 60. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figure 
<number box="[294,327,272,298]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,951,311,338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,418]" box="[197,951,311,338]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,357,311,337]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is known only from the type-locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,418]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,351,377]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the Brazilian entomologist Dr. João M. F. Camargo, eminent 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Meliponinae">Meliponinae</taxonomicName>
bee systematist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
